The paper deals with the problem of depth estimation and relative localization of ground robots using computer vision, which is a topic that falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a framework that uses a filter to compute the relative pose between the robots, which involves system identification and control theory (cs.SY). The use of continuous estimation techniques also suggests the involvement of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and statistical learning (cs.LG) in the proposed framework.
